HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 360
BY REPRESENTATIVE EDMONSTON
CHILDREN: Creates the Task Force on Child Well-Being, Parental Rights, and Family
Court Fairness
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To create the Task Force on Child Well-Being, Parental Bonds, and Family Court Fairness
3 to study the administration of justice in family courts, including but not limited to
4 disparities in custody outcomes.
5 WHEREAS, the family court system and district courts sitting in child custody
6 matters play a critical role in determining custody, visitation, and parental rights, and such
7 determinations directly affect the safety, stability, and long-term well-being of children; and
8 WHEREAS, the "best interest of the child" standard requires careful, consistent, and
9 evidence-based judicial decision making that preserves meaningful relationships between
10 children and fit parents whenever possible; and
11 WHEREAS, concerns have been raised regarding disparities in custody outcomes
12 across similar cases within family courts, including questions of consistency and
13 predictability in judicial determinations; and
14 WHEREAS, questions have been raised regarding due process protections afforded
15 to parents in family court proceedings, including the adequacy of notice and opportunity to
16 be heard prior to the issuance of temporary or ex parte orders affecting custody and
17 visitation; and
18 WHEREAS, concerns have been expressed regarding the evidentiary standards
19 utilized in custody and visitation determinations, including the reliance on limited or
20 incomplete evidence in certain proceedings; and
