1 WHEREAS, ex parte orders issued on the basis of allegations made by one parent
2 against another parent have significant and immediate effects on parent-child relationships
3 and may remain in place for extended periods pending further proceedings, thereby denying
4 a child the love and affection of a parent without the normal evidentiary process that every
5 other court requires; and
6 WHEREAS, the financial costs associated with custody litigation, including attorney
7 fees, expert evaluations, and related court expenses, may impose substantial burdens on
8 families and may limit access to justice; and
9 WHEREAS, it is in the public interest of this state to ensure that family court
10 proceedings are conducted in a manner that is fair, transparent, evidence based, and
11 consistent with constitutional protections and the best interests of children; and
12 WHEREAS, a comprehensive review of these issues is necessary to evaluate whether
13 statutory or procedural reforms are warranted to improve fairness, consistency, due process,
14 and child well-being outcomes in family courts.
15 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
16 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby establish and provide for the Task Force on Child
17 Well-Being, Parental Bonds, and Family Court Fairness to study the administration of justice
18 in family courts, including disparities in custody outcomes.
19 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that in its study, the task force shall consider all of
20 the following:
21 (1) Concerns regarding due process protections for parents.
22 (2) The adequacy of evidentiary standards used in custody and visitation
23 determinations, including ex parte orders issued without notice and the impact of such orders
24 on child well-being and parent-child bonds.
25 (3) The impact of rising costs of custody litigation and related proceedings on
26 families.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall consist of the following
28 members:
29 (1) The state representative who represents House District No. 88.
